{
  "video_id": "IBf9pXOmpFw",
  "title": "Why the pencil is perfect | Small Thing Big Idea, a TED series",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Krystian Aparta Reviewer: Camille Martínez"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 12198.0,
      "end_time": 15563.0,
      "text": "The sound is a really big part, I think, of the experience of using a pencil,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 15588.0,
      "end_time": 19640.0,
      "text": "and it has this really audible scratchiness."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 19880.0,
      "end_time": 21290.0,
      "text": "(Scratching)"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 22286.0,
      "end_time": 24806.0,
      "text": "[Small thing. Big idea.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25985.0,
      "end_time": 28313.0,
      "text": "[Caroline Weaver on the Pencil]"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 28556.0,
      "end_time": 30926.0,
      "text": "The pencil is a very simple object."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 30950.0,
      "end_time": 33435.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s made of wood with some layers of paint"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 33459.0,
      "end_time": 34975.0,
      "text": "an eraser and a core,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 34999.0,
      "end_time": 37395.0,
      "text": "which is made out of graphite, clay and water."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 37419.0,
      "end_time": 39950.0,
      "text": "Yeah, it took hundreds of people over centuries"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 39975.0,
      "end_time": 41651.0,
      "text": "to come to this design."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 41675.0,
      "end_time": 44955.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s that long history of collaboration"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 44980.0,
      "end_time": 47638.0,
      "text": "that, to me, makes it a very perfect object."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 48750.0,
      "end_time": 50349.0,
      "text": "The story of the pencil starts with graphite."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 50373.0,
      "end_time": 53290.0,
      "text": "People started finding really useful applications"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 53314.0,
      "end_time": 54925.0,
      "text": "for this new substance."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 54949.0,
      "end_time": 57107.0,
      "text": "They cut it into small sticks"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 57131.0,
      "end_time": 59599.0,
      "text": "and wrapped it in string or sheepskin or paper"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 59623.0,
      "end_time": 61617.0,
      "text": "and sold it on the streets of London"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 61641.0,
      "end_time": 63797.0,
      "text": "to be used for writing or for drawing"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 63821.0,
      "end_time": 66313.0,
      "text": "or, a lot of times, by farmers and shepherds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 66337.0,
      "end_time": 67996.0,
      "text": "who used it to mark their animals."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 68200.0,
      "end_time": 69262.0,
      "text": "Over in France,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 69287.0,
      "end_time": 73441.0,
      "text": "Nicolas-Jacques Conté figured out a method of grinding the graphite,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 73465.0,
      "end_time": 76584.0,
      "text": "mixing it with powdered clay and water to make a paste."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 76608.0,
      "end_time": 79777.0,
      "text": "From there, this paste was filled into a mold and fired in a kiln,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 79801.0,
      "end_time": 82751.0,
      "text": "and the result was a really strong graphite core"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 82775.0,
      "end_time": 85894.0,
      "text": "that wasn&#39;t breakable, that was smooth, usable --"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 85918.0,
      "end_time": 89140.0,
      "text": "it was so much better than anything else that existed at the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 89380.0,
      "end_time": 92848.0,
      "text": "and to this day, that&#39;s the method that&#39;s still used in making pencils."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 93461.0,
      "end_time": 96588.0,
      "text": "Meanwhile, over in America, in Concord, Massachusetts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 96612.0,
      "end_time": 99660.0,
      "text": "it was Henry David Thoreau who came up with the grading scale"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 99684.0,
      "end_time": 101770.0,
      "text": "for different hardnesses of pencil."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 101794.0,
      "end_time": 103717.0,
      "text": "It was graded one through four,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 103741.0,
      "end_time": 107392.0,
      "text": "number two being the ideal hardness for general use."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 107416.0,
      "end_time": 109966.0,
      "text": "The softer the pencil, the more graphite it had in it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 109990.0,
      "end_time": 112354.0,
      "text": "and the darker and smoother the line will be."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 113495.0,
      "end_time": 115782.0,
      "text": "The firmer the pencil, the more clay it had in it"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 115806.0,
      "end_time": 117816.0,
      "text": "and the lighter and finer it will be."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 118607.0,
      "end_time": 121774.0,
      "text": "Originally, when pencils were handmade, they were made round."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 121798.0,
      "end_time": 123472.0,
      "text": "There was no easy way to make them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 123496.0,
      "end_time": 126758.0,
      "text": "and it was the Americans who really mechanized the craft."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 126782.0,
      "end_time": 128728.0,
      "text": "A lot of people credit Joseph Dixon"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 128752.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132440.0,
      "text": "for being one of the first people to start developing actual machines"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 132464.0,
      "end_time": 136371.0,
      "text": "to do things like cut wood slats, cut grooves into the wood,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 136395.0,
      "end_time": 137604.0,
      "text": "apply glue to them ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 137628.0,
      "end_time": 140439.0,
      "text": "And they figured out it was easier and less wasteful"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 140463.0,
      "end_time": 142900.0,
      "text": "to do a hexagonal pencil,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 142115.0,
      "end_time": 143973.0,
      "text": "and so that became the standard."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 144558.0,
      "end_time": 146120.0,
      "text": "Since the early days of pencils,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 146145.0,
      "end_time": 148210.0,
      "text": "people have loved that they can be erased."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 149942.0,
      "end_time": 151510.0,
      "text": "Originally, it was bread crumbs"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 151534.0,
      "end_time": 153617.0,
      "text": "that were used to scratch away pencil marks"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 153641.0,
      "end_time": 155209.0,
      "text": "and later, rubber and pumice."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 155675.0,
      "end_time": 158967.0,
      "text": "The attached eraser happened in 1858,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 158991.0,
      "end_time": 162948.0,
      "text": "when American stationer Hymen Lipman patented the first pencil"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 162972.0,
      "end_time": 164354.0,
      "text": "with an attached eraser,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 164378.0,
      "end_time": 166250.0,
      "text": "which really changed the pencil game."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 166965.0,
      "end_time": 170359.0,
      "text": "The world&#39;s first yellow pencil was the KOH-I-NOOR 1500."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 170383.0,
      "end_time": 171888.0,
      "text": "KOH-I-NOOR did this crazy thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 171912.0,
      "end_time": 174825.0,
      "text": "where they painted this pencil with 14 coats of yellow paint"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 174849.0,
      "end_time": 176781.0,
      "text": "and dipped the end in 14-carat gold."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 177442.0,
      "end_time": 179160.0,
      "text": "There is a pencil for everyone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 179400.0,
      "end_time": 181447.0,
      "text": "and every pencil has a story."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 182460.0,
      "end_time": 186424.0,
      "text": "The Blackwing 602 is famous for being used by a lot of writers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 186449.0,
      "end_time": 189409.0,
      "text": "especially John Steinbeck and Vladimir Nabokov."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 189433.0,
      "end_time": 192370.0,
      "text": "And then, you have the Dixon pencil company."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 192610.0,
      "end_time": 194998.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re responsible for the Dixon Ticonderoga."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 195220.0,
      "end_time": 196173.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s an icon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 196197.0,
      "end_time": 198724.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s what people think of when they think of a pencil"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 198748.0,
      "end_time": 201171.0,
      "text": "and what they think of when they think of school."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 201195.0,
      "end_time": 203409.0,
      "text": "And the pencil&#39;s really a thing that, I think,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 203433.0,
      "end_time": 205910.0,
      "text": "the average user has never thought twice about,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 205934.0,
      "end_time": 208790.0,
      "text": "how it&#39;s made or why it&#39;s made the way it is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 208103.0,
      "end_time": 210470.0,
      "text": "because it&#39;s just always been that way."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 211500.0,
      "end_time": 213284.0,
      "text": "In my opinion, there&#39;s nothing that can be done"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 213308.0,
      "end_time": 215172.0,
      "text": "to make the pencil better than it is."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 216267.0,
      "end_time": 217417.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s perfect."
    }
  ]
}